data.enText: an emphatic statement, answer, etc. is given with force to show that it is important

data.chText: 明确表示的；加强语气的
data.enText: making it very clear what you mean by speaking with force

data.chText: 他强调他不能与她共事。
data.enText: He was emphatic that he could not work with her.
an emphatic victory, win, or defeat is one in which one team or player wins by a large amount
She is emphatically opposed to the proposals.

data.chText: 他一直断然否认这些指控。
data.enText: He has always emphatically denied the allegations.

data.chText: 这个建议已被断然否决。

tr: forceful and definite in expression or action
example: the document contained a particularly emphatic guarantee of religious liberty

value.def: An emphatic response or statement is one made in a forceful way, because the speaker feels very strongly about what they are saying.

example.ex: His response was immediate and emphatic...
I answered both questions with an emphatic 'Yes'.
example.tran: 对于那两个问题，我都语气坚定地回答“是”。

value.tran: 强调的;着重的;加强语气的

value.def: If you are emphatic about something, you use forceful language which shows that you feel very strongly about what you are saying.

example.ex: The rebels are emphatic that this is not a surrender...
example.tran: 叛乱者坚称这并不是投降。

example.ex: He is especially emphatic about the value of a precise routine.
example.tran: 他特别强调严格按程序走的意义。

gramarinfo.label: v-link ADJ, oft ADJ that, ADJ <l>about</l> n

value.tran: 措词强烈的;断然的;坚决的

value.def: An emphatic win or victory is one in which the winner has won by a large amount or distance.

example.ex: Yesterday's emphatic victory was their fifth in succession.
example.tran: 昨天的大胜是他们连续第5场胜利。
